    <fullPolicyText>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "markup": "<p data-start=\"338\" data-end=\"596\">We rely on accurate timekeeping to ensure everyone is paid fairly and in compliance with federal and state wage and hour laws. All employees—particularly those classified as non-exempt—must follow our established timekeeping procedures.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"598\" data-end=\"601\">\n<h4 data-start=\"603\" data-end=\"638\"><strong data-start=\"608\" data-end=\"636\">For Non-Exempt Employees</strong></h4>\n<p data-start=\"639\" data-end=\"710\">You are required to accurately record the following for each workday:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"711\" data-end=\"847\">\n<li data-start=\"711\" data-end=\"749\">\n<p data-start=\"713\" data-end=\"749\">Start and end times for your shift</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"750\" data-end=\"797\">\n<p data-start=\"752\" data-end=\"797\">Start and end times for unpaid meal periods</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"798\" data-end=\"847\">\n<p data-start=\"800\" data-end=\"847\">All hours worked beyond your regular schedule</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"849\" data-end=\"969\">Working “off the clock” is strictly prohibited. All hours worked must be recorded and will be compensated accordingly.</p>\n<p data-start=\"971\" data-end=\"1166\">All overtime must be approved in advance by your manager unless otherwise authorized. While unapproved overtime may still be paid, it may result in performance discussions or disciplinary action.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1168\" data-end=\"1355\">Falsifying, omitting, or altering your own time records or those of another employee is a serious violation of policy and may result in corrective action, up to and including termination.</p>\n<hr data-start=\"1357\" data-end=\"1360\">\n<h4 data-start=\"1362\" data-end=\"1393\"><strong data-start=\"1367\" data-end=\"1391\">For Exempt Employees</strong></h4>\n<p data-start=\"1394\" data-end=\"1479\">Exempt employees are not required to record daily hours worked but may be asked to:</p>\n<ul data-start=\"1480\" data-end=\"1618\">\n<li data-start=\"1480\" data-end=\"1528\">\n<p data-start=\"1482\" data-end=\"1528\">Log any use of paid time off or unpaid leave</p>\n</li>\n<li data-start=\"1529\" data-end=\"1618\">\n<p data-start=\"1531\" data-end=\"1618\">Confirm attendance during certain periods for audit, compliance, or operational needs</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"1620\" data-end=\"1834\">If you have any questions about what counts as working time or how to track your time correctly, please speak with your manager or the HR team. Accurate time records help ensure timely and correct pay for everyone.</p>",
